  "body": "After starting a backup on a large database, the last thing I see logged is this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nI0808 21:08:56.605378 xtrabackupengine.go:118] Detected MySQL flavor: MySQL56\r\n```\r\n\r\nI can see from network traffic that it's uploading something, so I assume it's running. However, it would be nice to print to the logs that the backup is starting. Ideally we could also ask xtrabackup to print progress to stderr, capture it, and pipe it to our own logs.\r\n\r\ncc @deepthi ",
